The uncertainty surrounding Mikel Arteta's future at Arsenal appears to have been lifted after the player's agent claimed he had signed a one-year contract extension at the Emirates.

The 32-year-old - who is currently sidelined with an ankle problem - arrived on a four-year deal in 2011, which was due to expire at the end of the season.

However, the Spaniard's agent Inaki Ibanez has told footmercato.net that his client will still be a Gunner next season.  'Mikel is no longer free next June, because he now has an extra year on his contract,' Ibanez said. 

Mikel Arteta (left) is staying at Arsenal for another season, according to the player's agent

