It has been reported that former club Everton were interested in convincing Arteta to return to Goodison Park.

Arteta has not played since limping off during Arsenal's 2-0 Champions League defeat of Borussia Dortmund in November and is not expected to return until April. 

The veteran playmaker was named club captain by Arsene Wenger following the departure of Thomas Vermaelen to Barcelona, but has made only seven Premier League appearances this season.

